node.text: If you’ve been feeling overwhelmed at work lately, you’re not alone. When we surveyed over 6,000 information and Firstline workers in eight countries, we found 30% of workers said the pandemic has increased their feelings of burnout at work. Inspired by this research and conversations with customers, we’re marking the start of a longer journey to evolve our productivity tools to promote individual wellbeing and organizational resilience. Learn more at the link in our bio.  #WorldMentalHealthDay

node.title: A Pulse on Employees’ Wellbeing- Six Months Into The Pandemic
